Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potato{450}(chopped into 2cm chunks) (no
need to peel!). Pop the potato on a low sided wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@olive oil{1}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread
out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf of your
oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread
> out.

== Breadcrumb Crust ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25}, @grated hard Italian style
cheese{40} and oil. Mix to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

== Hake ==

Pat the @hake fillets{2} with #kitchen paper{} to remove any excess moisture. Lay
the hake fillets onto a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Drizzle with
oil and season with salt and pepper. Divide the breadcrumb mix evenly between
the two fillets and press down firmly to keep in place. Pop on the top shelf of
the oven and bake until the crumb is golden and the fish is cooked through,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when it is opaque all the way though.

== Paprika Mayo ==

Meanwhile in a separate small bowl mix the @mayonnaise{2}, @smoked paprika{1}
and @water{1}. Season with salt and pepper and set to one side for later.

== Broccoli ==

Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Peel and grate the
@garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle
of oil in a #frying pan{} on a high heat, once hot add the broccoli, and fry,
constantly stirring, until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Then add the garlic and a
splash of water. Cover with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{} and cook until tender,
~{4-5%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Share the roasted potatoes among your plates. Serve the hake and broccoli
alongside and drizzle over the paprika mayo. Enjoy!